article.headline: Forrest, Sebree lead FAU past Tampa 84-35
article.linkText: Forrest, Sebree lead FAU past Tampa 84-35
article.story: BOCA RATON, Fla. -- Michael Forrest scored 15 points to lead five Florida Atlantic players in double figures as the Owls won their seventh straight home game, routing Tampa 84-35 on Thursday night. Jaylen Sebree added 11 points for the Owls. Jailyn Ingram, D.J. Robertson and Cornelius Taylor each had 10. The Division II Spartans' 35 points on 25.0 percent shooting (11-for-44) represented the worst marks by a Florida Atlantic opponent this season. Pat Bacon had 15 points for the Spartans. Gio Diaz added 11 points. Martin Lakovic had 4 points.
